# ==========================================================
# HOOK TYPE: PRE-COMMIT (Client-Side Shield)
# TOOL: Husky + lint-staged (v16.4.0)
# VERSION: v9.1.7 (Stable)
# PRE-COMMIT CONFIGURATION
# DOCUMENTATION: https://typicode.github.io/husky
# PURPOSE: Blocking invalid or insecure code before a commit is created
# USE CASES:
#   1. Quality: Auto-fix linting (ESLint) & formatting (Prettier).
#   2. Security: Pattern-scan for secrets (Gitleaks) in staged diffs
# EXECUTION:
#   - MODE: Blocking (Exit code 1 on failure)
#   - PERFORMANCE: Uses lint-staged to only scan modified files
# SCOPE:
#   - Staged files
# CONTEXT: 
#   - Stack: Vite + pnpm + Vue/React
# SECURITY NOTES:
#   - Prevents secrets from entering local history
#   - WARNING: Can be bypassed via --no-verify
#   - CAUTION: Husky is disable in CI/CD
# DEPENDENCIES:
#   - gitleaks.toml → Defines gitleaks rules
#   - package.json#config.lint-staged → lint-staged config
# MAINTENANCE:
#   - Update version quarterly
#   - Review if Update stylelint/eslint/prettier
#   - Owner: @gituser
# ==========================================================


#!/bin/sh

echo "Running pre-commit checks..."

echo "Checking secrets..."
gitleaks protect --staged --verbose

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "❌ Secrets detected! Commit blocked."
  exit 1
fi

echo "Running lint checks..."
pnpm lint-staged
